<body>
    <div class="navbar">Enrollment Restrictions in Intune</div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="section">
            <h2>1. Device Type Restrictions</h2>
            <p>Control which types of devices can enroll in Intune.</p>
            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>Go to **Microsoft Intune Admin Center**.</li>
                <li>Navigate to **Devices → Enrollment restrictions**.</li>
                <li>Set restrictions for platforms like Android, iOS, Windows, and macOS.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="section">
            <h2>2. Device Limit Restrictions</h2>
            <p>Set the number of devices a user can enroll.</p>
            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>In the **Intune Admin Center**, go to **Devices → Enrollment restrictions**.</li>
                <li>Set a limit for how many devices each user can enroll.</li>
                <li>Save the configuration to enforce restrictions.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
